    "body": "The current check for `currentSpillableSize` where we want to make sure the store's spillable count is above the target size, can prevent us from spilling anything and makes big assumptions that what is in the store is not contributing to fragmentation. \r\n\r\nWe do not want to check `currentSpillableSize` at all, and instead we want to just spill at least one buffer and let the allocation retry (per @jlowe's comment here: https://github.com/NVIDIA/spark-rapids/pull/7572#discussion_r1100314872). \r\n\r\nNote that we also want to look at prioritizing the spillables based on size: https://github.com/NVIDIA/spark-rapids/issues/7705, which is related to the heuristic here.",
